    "body": "The default behavior of `limit=None` and a `limit_direction` is now to go to the end of the sequence:\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn [70]: ser.interpolate(limit_direction='backward', limit=None)\r\nOut[70]:\r\n0     5.000000\r\n1     5.000000\r\n2     5.000000\r\n3     7.666667\r\n4    10.333333\r\n5    13.000000\r\n6          NaN\r\n7          NaN\r\ndtype: float64\r\n\r\nIn [71]: ser.interpolate(limit_direction='both', limit=None)\r\nOut[71]:\r\n0     5.000000\r\n1     5.000000\r\n2     5.000000\r\n3     7.666667\r\n4    10.333333\r\n5    13.000000\r\n6    13.000000\r\n7    13.000000\r\ndtype: float64\r\n\r\nIn [72]: pd.__version__\r\nOut[72]: '0.24.0.dev0+780.g145c2275e'\r\n```"
